
2015 International Conference on Speech Technology and Human-Computer Dialogue, SpeD 2015




 
The proceedings contain 29 papers. The topics discussed include: achievements in the field of voice synthesis for Romanian; estimating competing speaker count for blind speech source separation; deep learning in acoustic modeling for automatic speech recognition and understanding - an overview; quantization effects on audio signals for detecting intruders in wild areas using TESPAR S-matrix and artificial neural networks; speech applications in the eWALL project; unsupervised aspect level sentiment analysis using ant clustering and self-organizing maps; database and system design for data collection of crying related to infant's needs and diseases; speech database acquisition for assisted living environment applications; methods for automatic generation of GRAALAN-based phonetic databases; and an internet slang annotated dictionary and its use in assessing message attitude and sentiments.


